OL,6,FDuring a hearing at Warwick Crown
OL,7,FCourt on Wednesday, at which Windsor
OL,8,Fwas not present, Judge Tom Rochford
OL,9,Fsaid he needed further information
OL,10,Ffrom the prosecution about the
OL,11,Favailability of bed spaces before he
OL,12,Fdecided whether to impose a prison
OL,13,Fsentence or hospital order.
OL,15,FThe judge said: "There are three
OL,16,Foptions ` imprisonment, which, looking
OL,17,Fat it, he may have served with time on
OL,18,Fremand, a hospital order without
OL,19,Frestriction, or a hospital order with
OL,20,Frestriction."
